Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.46,0:00:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,两周前\NTwo weeks ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.33,0:00:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,一个隐形穹顶罩住了切斯特磨坊镇\Nan invisible dome crashed down on Chester's Mill,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.39,0:00:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,使我们与世隔绝\Ncutting us off from the rest of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.35,0:00:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么穹顶会在这里  以后还会有什么谜团\NWhy the dome is here or what mysteries lie ahead,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.04,0:00:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,我们依然一无所知\Nwe still don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.26,0:00:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,每天它都考验我们的极限\NEvery day it tests our limits,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.74,0:00:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,激发我们内心最善和最恶一面\Nbringing out the best and the worst in us.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.08,0:00:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,有人说我们会永远困在这里\NSome say we'll be stuck here forever,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.87,0:00:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,但我们会一直奋力寻找出路\Nbut we will never stop fighting to find a way out.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.67,0:00:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,丽贝卡·佩恩觉得切斯特磨坊镇\NRebecca Pine thinks Chester's Mill
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.10,0:00:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,维持不了多久全镇居民的供给\Ncan't sustain itself for much longer,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.08,0:00:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,她和吉姆想通过人口调查\Nand she and Jim want to use the census
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.09,0:00:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,来决定大家的生死\Nto decide who lives and who doesn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.13,0:00:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,猪流感就是他们的灭绝计划\NThat pig virus is their extermination plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.23,0:00:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,对  而且她不知道那效力有多大\NYeah, and she doesn't know how strong it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.73,0:00:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,离我远点\NGet away from me!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.74,0:00:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,你想杀了我们\NYou tried to us all!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.75,0:00:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,你在这里干什么\NWhat are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.85,0:00:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,她要跟你一起进监狱\NShe's joining you in jail.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.35,0:00:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,你打算怎么对付我们\NWhat are you gonna do to us?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.64,0:00:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,明天我们会召开镇民大会\NTomorrow we'll have a town meeting
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.87,0:00:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,人们来决定你们的命运\Nand the people can decide your fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.60,0:00:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,你是来放我出去的\NYou came to set me free.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.61,0:00:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,我妈妈说你有答案  我想知道\NMy mother said you had answers; I want them.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.97,0:00:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,是这个  是吗\NThis is it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.34,0:00:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,抱歉  孩子\NSorry, kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.94,0:00:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,那些是手指印\NThose are the fingertips of a hand--
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.83,0:00:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,似乎安琪也留下了一点凶手的战利品\NLooks like Angie got a piece of whoever did this to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.75,0:01:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,你觉得呢  菲尔\NWhat do you say, Phil?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.74,0:01:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,我能信任你吗\NCan I count on you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.91,0:01:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,我就是梅兰妮·克洛斯\NI am Melanie Cross.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.99,0:01:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,我应该是死在了这里\NAnd I think this is where I died.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.85,0:01:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,天啊  我们得去帮她\NOh, my God, we have to help her.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.84,0:01:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,我们帮不了了\NI don't think we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.99,0:01:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,-太晚了  -她要死了\N- It's too late. - She's dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.95,0:01:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,你们在干什么\NWhat are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.40,0:01:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,你刚才在呻吟\NYou were moaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.12,0:01:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,做恶梦了吗\NNightmare?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.15,0:01:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,不是  只是普通的梦\NNo. Just a dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.49,0:01:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,并没有醒来以后看到你俩站在我面前那么恐怖\NNot as scary as waking up to you two standing over me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.48,0:01:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,我们这几天都没有睡好\NNone of us sleep very well these days.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.09,0:01:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,我需要找到山姆·维多\NI need to find Sam Verdreaux.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.33,0:01:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,查清楚我死的那晚到底发生了什么\NFind out what really happened the night I died.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.00,0:01:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道你想要答案\NI know you want some answers,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.79,0:01:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,但我们答应芭比了\Nbut we promised Barbie
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.63,0:01:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,在他跟茱莉亚谈完之前我们不会做任何事\Nwe wouldn't do anything until after he talks to Julia.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.98,0:02:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,我需要跟你谈谈\NI need to talk to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.97,0:02:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,我得去找我们的神秘女孩\NI need to find our mystery girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.01,0:02:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,她昨晚没回家\NShe didn't come home last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.43,0:02:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,梅兰妮跟乔和诺莉待在一起\NMelanie stayed with Joe and Norrie.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.24,0:02:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,梅兰妮  你怎么知道她的名字\NMelanie? How do you know her name?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.86,0:02:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,说来话长\NIt's a long story.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.85,0:02:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,你不会刚好知道山姆在哪里吧  对吗\NYou wouldn't happen to know where Sam is, would you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.84,0:02:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,他刚刚离开\NHe just left.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.24,0:02:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,我们通宵工作来着\NWe were up all night, working.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.45,0:02:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,你找山姆干什么\NWhy are you looking for Sam?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.65,0:02:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,因为我认为他一直认识梅兰妮\NBecause I think he's known who Melanie is all along.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.62,0:02:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,告诉我所有的事\NAll right, tell me everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.66,0:02:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,孩子们在学校年鉴上找到了她的照片\NThe kids found her picture in the school yearbook.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.71,0:02:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,-那她是这里的学生吗  -曾经是\N- So, she's a student here? - Was.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.55,0:02:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,1988年的\NIn 1988.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.10,0:02:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道\NI know.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.15,0:02:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我还在消化这一切\NI'm still processing all of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.80,0:02:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,她还知道乔和诺莉在哪里找到的迷你穹顶\NShe also knows exactly where Joe and Norrie found the mini-dome.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.69,0:02:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,怎么知道的\NHow?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.36,0:02:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,25年前  她和她的三个朋友发现一颗陨石\N25 years ago, she and three of her friends found a meteorite
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.39,0:02:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,里面有颗蛋  迷你穹顶也刚好在\Nin exactly the same spot in the woods
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.70,0:02:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,树林里的那个位置\Nwith an egg inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.08,0:02:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,梅兰妮说当她找到它时\NMelanie said that when she found it,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.95,0:02:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,她想要保护它  但其他人变得暴躁起来\Nthat she wanted to protect it, and the others got violent.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.90,0:02:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,然后  她的一个朋友杀死了她\NAnd then, one of her friends killed her.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.87,0:02:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,她不知道是谁\NShe's not sure who.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.44,0:02:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,她的三个朋友都是谁\NWho were the three friends?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.71,0:03:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,波琳·维多  莱尔·夏姆利\NPauline Verdreaux, Lyle Chumley
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.93,0:03:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,还有山姆\Nand Sam.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.39,0:03:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,这太疯狂了\NThis is crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.39,0:03:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,这在切斯特磨坊镇是常有的事\NThis is just par for the course for Chester's Mill.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.83,0:03:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我们需要谈谈另一天发生的事\NAnd we need to talk about what happened the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.24,0:03:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,关于你支持吉姆和丽贝卡的灭绝计划的事吗\NAbout your supporting Jim and Rebecca's extermination plot?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.07,0:03:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,你怎么会觉得我真会支持呢\NHow could you think that I would actually do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.53,0:03:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,-因为我当时在场  -我那是在听他们说\N- Because I was there. - I was listening
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.17,0:03:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,才能知道他们到底要做些什么\Nso I could make sure that I knew exactly what they were up to,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.97,0:03:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,才可以去阻止他们\Nso I could stop them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.51,0:03:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,我让吉姆看着我的眼睛\NI made Jim look me in the eye
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.52,0:03:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,向我承诺他不会做任何事\Nand promise me that he wasn't gonna do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.30,0:03:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,我才不信\NI don't know that I believe that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.81,0:03:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你想要把我当成坏人\NIf you want to think that I'm the bad guy,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.31,0:03:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,随你\Nthen fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.99,0:03:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,做好山姆·维多更糟糕的准备吧\NBe prepared to think far worse of Sam Verdreaux.
